 {"id":"franken_numpy-w4zs.3","title":"Optimize general broadcast odometer path with specialized loops","description":"The general broadcast path uses an 'odometer' pattern to compute indices dynamically. This is slow for large arrays. Optimizations:
1. Add skip-error-check fast path when all modes are Ignore
2. Specialize for common ops (Add/Sub/Mul/Div) to avoid op.apply() dispatch
3. Consider pre-computing stride patterns for common broadcast scenarios

This complements franken_numpy-w4zs.1 (same-shape) and franken_numpy-w4zs.2 (tail-contiguous broadcast).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-04-15T00:49:38.678219010Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-15T00:54:37.895976031Z","closed_at":"2026-04-15T00:54:37.895976031Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["optimization","performance"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"franken_numpy-w4zs.3","depends_on_id":"franken_numpy-w4zs","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-15T00:49:38.678219010Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
