 {"id":"franken_numpy-w9bw","title":"Test compilation failures in fnp-python due to pyo3 unbind and type inference","description":"Running cargo test on fnp-python fails with multiple E0599 errors: 'no method named unbind found for struct pyo3::Py<T>'. Calls like '1_i64.into_pyobject(py)?.unbind().into_any().unbind()' are invalid in PyO3 0.21+. Additionally, there is an E0282 type inference error where the type of 'input.bind(py)' cannot be inferred in 'numeric_array(py, input.bind(py), dtype)'. Please fix these compilation errors in the fnp-python tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-18T18:28:53.883823986Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-18T18:37:27.680620004Z","closed_at":"2026-04-18T18:37:27.678754412Z","close_reason":"Non-reproducible on current tree: rch cargo check -p fnp-python --tests passes and the cited bad PyO3 patterns are absent","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
